    <string name="dashboard_info_title">Dashboard</string>
    <string name="dashboard_info">• Tap a device action to run it\n• Choose list or widget view when there is enough space for readable widgets\n• Arrows change the order\n• The X at the bottom right cancels a running action\n• Action details: tap the compact bar to open it, or its title to minimize it\n• Green: Wi-Fi connection confirmed\n• Red: a specific Wi-Fi connection attempt failed\n• Gray: Wi-Fi not yet confirmed, no assignment, or detection unavailable\n• A visible SSID does not confirm a connection\n• The menu opens settings, updates, help, and About SwitchWerk</string>
    <string name="settings_info">• Wi-Fi profiles: manage credentials\n• Devices: define actions and Wi-Fi assignments\n• System: appearance, updates, action details, and external intents\n• Configurations: export or import the configuration</string>
    <string name="system_info_title">System</string>
    <string name="system_info">• Choose appearance and language\n• Check for updates and open GitHub release notes\n• Show or hide action details\n• Allow or block external intents</string>
    <string name="backup_info">• Export saves the local configuration\n• Import loads a configuration from a trusted source\n• Choose password handling deliberately for each action\n• The password choice applies only to the next action and is reset afterwards</string>
    <string name="password_storage_info">Wi-Fi passwords are stored encrypted on this device. They are not sent to a cloud service and are not shown in action details.</string>
    <string name="hostname_ip_info">Enter the device\'s local address in its assigned Wi-Fi network, for example 192.168.33.1 or a hostname resolved on the local network. No internet connection is required.</string>
    <string name="api_call_info">The HTTP/RPC call is appended to the local device address. Use only a path supported by the device. POST can send an optional request body with a Content-Type, for example /relay/0?turn=on.</string>
    <string name="action_details_info">• Shows Wi-Fi connection, timeout, and HTTP status\n• Layout values remain available as the oldest scrollable log entry\n• The X at the bottom right cancels the running action\n• Tap the compact bar to open it\n• Tap the Action details title in the open panel to minimize it\n• Local progress only\n• Passwords are not logged</string>
    <string name="wifi_profiles_info_title">Manage Wi-Fi profiles</string>
    <string name="devices_info_title">Manage devices</string>
    <string name="list_interaction_info">• Use + to add an entry\n• Tap an entry to edit it\n• Swipe left or right to delete it\n• Confirm deletion afterwards</string>
    <string name="wifi_profile_dialog_info_title">Wi-Fi profile</string>
    <string name="wifi_profile_dialog_info">• Enter the target Wi-Fi SSID\n• The name must be unique\n• The password remains encrypted on the device</string>
    <string name="device_dialog_info_title">Device</string>
    <string name="device_dialog_info">• Set the name and button label\n• Optionally offer the action as an app shortcut\n• Android shows at most four enabled shortcuts in dashboard order\n• Choose HTTP or HTTPS\n• Enter the HTTP/RPC method and path\n• For POST, optionally choose request body and Content-Type\n• Wi-Fi assignments define the connection order</string>
    <string name="app_shortcut">App shortcut</string>
    <string name="app_shortcut_description">Offer this device action when the app icon is long-pressed. Android shows at most four selected actions.</string>
    <string name="help_shortcuts_title">App shortcuts</string>
    <string name="help_shortcuts_text">• Enable an action in its device dialog\n• Long-press the app icon and select the action\n• At most four enabled actions are offered in dashboard order\n• Progress and results appear on the dashboard</string>
    <string name="help_external_intents_title">External intents</string>
    <string name="help_external_intents_text">• Enable external intents in Settings → System\n• Find the stable local device ID in an exported configuration\n• Only an existing local device ID is accepted\n• URLs, commands, request bodies, and additional extras are rejected\n• The intent opens SwitchWerk in the foreground\n• Progress and results appear on the dashboard\n• Error notices disappear automatically but remain in Action details until cleared</string>
    <string name="help_external_intents_examples_title">Copyable ADB examples</string>
    <string name="help_external_intents_examples_text">Valid device action (replace device-123 with the local device ID):\nadb shell am start -n de.piecha.switchwerk/.MainActivity -a de.piecha.switchwerk.action.RUN_DEVICE_ACTION --es de.piecha.switchwerk.extra.DEVICE_ID device-123\n\nMissing device ID (error test):\nadb shell am start -n de.piecha.switchwerk/.MainActivity -a de.piecha.switchwerk.action.RUN_DEVICE_ACTION</string>
    <string name="external_intents_title">External intents</string>
    <string name="external_intents_enable">Allow external intents</string>
    <string name="external_intents_description">Disabled by default. Other apps can start configured device actions by local ID only. Error notices disappear automatically and remain in Action details until cleared.</string>
    <string name="external_intent_disabled_error">External intents are disabled in Settings.</string>
    <string name="external_intent_missing_device_id_error">The external intent has no device ID.</string>
    <string name="external_intent_unknown_device_error">The external intent references an unknown device.</string>
    <string name="external_intent_invalid_error">The external intent is invalid and was rejected.</string>
    <string name="wifi_assignment_dialog_info_title">Wi-Fi assignment</string>
    <string name="wifi_assignment_dialog_info">• Select a Wi-Fi profile for the device\n• Enter the local device address\n• No internet access is required</string>
    <string name="about_switchwerk">About SwitchWerk</string>
    <string name="about_description">SwitchWerk switches Wi-Fi devices that are not part of another network and cannot be reached through it. If these devices provide their own small Wi-Fi network, SwitchWerk can connect to it and trigger actions. You need to know which actions the devices support; this information is usually available from the manufacturer or relevant internet forums.\n\nYour configuration stays on this device. SwitchWerk works locally and does not require accounts, cloud services or tracking.</string>
    <string name="version_value">Version %1$s</string>
    <string name="about_author">Developed by Sebastian Piecha</string>
    <string name="about_license">License: GNU AGPL-3.0-or-later</string>
    <string name="open_github_project">Open GitHub project</string>
    <string name="help_getting_started_title">Setup</string>
    <string name="help_getting_started_text">• Existing configuration: open Settings → Configurations and import a configuration\n• Manual setup 1: create the Wi-Fi profiles SwitchWerk should connect to in Settings → Wi-Fi Profiles\n• Manual setup 2: create devices in Settings → Devices and assign them to a Wi-Fi profile\n• Trigger the configured actions on the Dashboard</string>
    <string name="help_connection_title">Connection and troubleshooting</string>
    <string name="help_connection_text">• The status point confirms a Wi-Fi connection, not physical Wi-Fi proximity\n• Green: Wi-Fi connection confirmed\n• Red: Android could not establish the specific Wi-Fi request\n• Gray: Wi-Fi not yet confirmed, no assignment, or detection unavailable\n• A visible SSID alone does not confirm a connection\n• The X at the bottom right cancels a running action and its Wi-Fi request\n• Android\'s system dialog cannot be closed by SwitchWerk\n• A device access point may interrupt internet access\n• HTTP errors come from the device</string>
    <string name="help_import_title">Save and load configurations</string>
    <string name="help_import_text">• Import configurations only from trusted sources\n• Export and import are clearly separated in Configurations\n• Wi-Fi profiles, devices and settings can be transferred\n• Password import and export must be selected deliberately before each action: left without passwords, right with passwords\n• The related action stays disabled in the middle position\n• The password choice applies only to the next action and is reset afterwards</string>
    <string name="help_privacy_title">Permissions and privacy</string>
    <string name="help_privacy_text">• Local operation only\n• No accounts, cloud, or tracking\n• Wi-Fi and location permissions only for Wi-Fi features</string>
    <string name="help_updates_title">Updates</string>
    <string name="help_updates_text">• Release updates are checked through the official GitHub project\n• GitHub release notes open the release page in the browser\n• Automatic checks run at most once per day\n• APK download and installation start only after user action</string>
    <string name="setup_wizard_title">Setup Wizard</string>
    <string name="setup_wizard_return_hint">When you open a linked page from this wizard, Back returns here until you close the wizard with one of the buttons at the bottom.</string>
    <string name="setup_wizard_intro_title">Introduction</string>
    <string name="setup_wizard_intro_text">SwitchWerk switches Wi-Fi devices that are not part of another network and cannot be reached through it.</string>
    <string name="setup_wizard_intro_steps">1. In Settings → Wi-Fi Profiles, configure the Wi-Fi networks SwitchWerk should connect to.\n2. In Settings → Devices, create devices and assign them to a Wi-Fi profile.\n3. On the app home screen (Dashboard), trigger the configured actions.</string>
    <string name="setup_wizard_status_lights_text">The colored LED-style indicators show the last known connection status: green means confirmed, red means the connection failed, and gray means unknown or not assigned. Treat them as guidance only, because Android policies can limit Wi-Fi detection and connection feedback.</string>
    <string name="setup_wizard_import_title">Do you want to import an existing configuration?</string>
    <string name="setup_wizard_import_text">Open Configurations if you want to load a prepared file, URL or QR code.</string>
    <string name="setup_wizard_manual_title">Do you want to set up devices yourself?</string>
    <string name="setup_wizard_manual_text">Use the three steps in order if you want to create Wi-Fi profiles and devices manually.</string>
